      "order": 1,
      "Description": "This lesson explores how artificial intelligence is being used to create, spread, and amplify misinformation across the internet. You will learn how AI-generated content, including realistic fake images, videos, and written articles, can be produced quickly and at scale, making it increasingly difficult to distinguish fact from fiction. We will look at real-world examples of how misinformation campaigns have gone viral and the role AI tools have played in accelerating their reach. By the end of this lesson, you will have a clearer understanding of the tactics used to manipulate public opinion online and why this matters in everyday life. No prior technical knowledge is required, just a curiosity about how the digital world around you is changing.",
